cast_shell: use the real ozone input-method context so the compositor OSK works

CastWindowManagerAura::Setup unconditionally calls
ui::InitializeInputMethodForTesting, which installs a
FakeInputMethodContext into the highest-precedence slot of the linux
input-method-context factory. That stub returns a null
VirtualKeyboardController and issues no wayland requests, so the real
WaylandInputMethodContext that ozone installs at InitializeUI is never
consulted. The result: focusing a web text field produces zero
text-input traffic to the compositor and no on-screen keyboard ever
shows.

Removing the call lets CreateLinuxInputMethodContext fall through to
the ozone factory and build the real WaylandInputMethodContext. With
--enable-wayland-ime --wayland-text-input-version=1 on the launcher,
focus then drives zwp_text_input_v1 activate + show_input_panel, which
is what makes weston launch its input-panel keyboard. The kiosk has no
test harness that depended on the fake context.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [kiosk-specific use case]

Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>

--- a/chromecast/graphics/cast_window_manager_aura.cc
+++ b/chromecast/graphics/cast_window_manager_aura.cc
@@ -182,8 +182,6 @@
   }
   DCHECK(display::Screen::Get());

-  ui::InitializeInputMethodForTesting();
-
   gfx::Rect host_bounds = GetPrimaryDisplayHostBounds();
   ui::PlatformWindowInitProperties properties(host_bounds);
